{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T15:19:22.591Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "You’re asking specifically about "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Pull Requests (PRs)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "code reviews"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in the Git workflow. Below is a practical, engineer-focused guide covering what they are, why they matter, best practices, and concrete templates you can use immediately."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Pull Requests & Reviews — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. What It Is"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Pull Request (PR)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": A proposal to merge one branch into another (usually into "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "main"}, {"type": "text", "text": "), with a description, discussion thread, and review process before merging."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Code Review"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": The human process of examining changes in a PR for correctness, design, tests, performance, and style."}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Why It Matters"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Quality Gate"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": PRs + reviews catch bugs and design issues before they hit production."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type